  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "French Baguettes. Classical French method, scaled to a home kitchen. Adjustable for what you need."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bread is mostly waiting. Mix, prove, shape, prove again, bake hot with steam."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What you need"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "defaultServings": 4,
          "items": [
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "plain-flour",
              "amount": 500,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "water",
              "amount": 360,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine",
              "amount": 10,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "yeast-dried",
              "amount": 3,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "honey",
              "amount": 25,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mix all ingredients in a bowl, cover with a plastic wrap and let rest for 15 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Over a period of 1 1/2 hours, do 3 sets of stretch and folds, flipping the dough upside down after each set."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cover the bowl with a plastic wrap and place in the refrigerator overnight for about 12-14 hours."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Turn the dough on a lightly floured work surface. Divide into 3 equal parts and shape into rectangles. Cover and let rest for 45-60 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Starting preheating the oven to 500F, with a baking stone positioned in the upper half of the oven and a bread pan filled with hot water on the bottom rack."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Stretch each dough rectangle slightly and fold into a cylinder, sealing the seams. Using your hands, roll the cylinders gently stretching them to desired length, about 14-15 inches."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Place on a lightly floured couche, seam side up. Cover and proof at a room temperature for about 30-60 minutes, or until the dough has sufficiently proofed."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Transfer the baguettes to a piece of parchment paper, seam side down and dust off excess flour. Using a bread lame, a sharp knife or a razor blade, make 3 scores on each baguette. When scoring, use a swift and firm motion to ensure nice and clean cuts."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Open the oven, taking caution not to get burned by steam, and slide the baguettes off onto the baking stone. Close the oven and reduce the temperature to 475 F. Bake for 15 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Remove the water pan, rotate the baguettes, drop the temperature to 450F and continue baking for another 15 minutes or until deep golden brown."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Bread is dense and didn't rise",
              "cause": "Yeast was stale, or the dough was too cold.",
              "fix": "Check yeast in warm water with a pinch of sugar — it should froth in five minutes. Prove in a warm spot (airing cupboard or oven with the light on)."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Crust is pale and soft",
              "cause": "Oven not hot enough, or no steam.",
              "fix": "Preheat to 220°C with a tray on the bottom. Throw a cup of water into the tray when the loaf goes in — steam gives crust."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Open crumb wasn't open",
              "cause": "Underproved, or the dough was knocked back too hard.",
              "fix": "Give it longer — until the dough doesn't spring back when poked. Shape gently so the bubbles survive."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Bottom burnt before top browned",
              "cause": "Tray was too thin, or rack too low.",
              "fix": "Bake on a heavier tray on the middle shelf. Lining with baking paper helps."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Seeded crust: brush the top with water and roll in mixed seeds before the final prove."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Wholemeal: replace 100 g of the flour with wholemeal for a denser, nuttier loaf."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Classical French cookery rests on this kind of dish — slow extraction, considered seasoning, restraint at the finish. Escoffier and the Larousse Gastronomique codified the method; cooks like Elizabeth David and Julia Child brought it into the English-language kitchen."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}